            <title>[SPARK-25472] Structured Streaming query.stop() doesn&apos;t always stop gracefully</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/SPARK-25472</link>
                <project id="12315420" key="SPARK">Spark</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;We can have race conditions where the cancelling of Spark jobs will throw a SparkException when stopping a streaming query. This SparkException specifies that the job was cancelled. We can use this error message to swallow the error.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
